The newly appointed Vice Chancellor of the University of Maiduguri, Prof. Aliyu Shugaba, will on Saturday, August 3, 2019, be conferred with the fellowship award and Icon of Excellent Diplomatic Leadership and Management Award of the Institute of Business Diplomacy and Financial Management of Nigeria (IBDFM). Speaking to newsmen in Abuja, Registrar and Secretary to the Council of the Institute, Mr. Sukana Danjuma Tusha, confirmed that the decision to confer the dual prestigious awards on Prof. Aliyu Shugaba was reached after an extensive consideration of his sterling leadership and management qualities. The programme, which is the 17th edition in the series, titled “ Managing Emotions in the Workplace” will have a prominent politician, Pharmacist, philanthropist and entrepreneur, Dr. Mike Omotosho as the chairman of the occasion while President and Chairman of Council, Prof. A.A. Aminu will preside over the programme. Business diplomacy institute to confer awards on VC Unimaid IBDFM announces date for mandatory prog UK institute confers fellowship on Zazzau emir, others Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin